Package org.livingdoc.converters

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooleanConverter
    This converter is used to convert a String to a boolean, if the String is "true" or "false"
    CharacterConverter
    This converter is used to convert a String with a length of 1 to a char
    JSONConverter<T>
    A TypeConverter to convert json strings into custom Types. This is not a Default TypeConverter and must always be explicitly specified to be used.
    StringConverter
    This converter is used to convert a String to a String
    TypeConverterManager
    This object manages interface TypeConverter instances. It has two responsibilities:
    TypeConverters
    Utility object providing interface TypeConverter related operations.
